q {
Q:"Two decks of playing cards are well shuffled and 26 cards are randomly distributed to a player. Then the probability that the player gets all distinct cards is:"
A:"d"
O:a) "\\(\\frac{\\binom{52}{26}}{\\binom{104}{26}}\\)", b) "\\(\\frac{2 \\times \\binom{52}{26}}{\\binom{104}{26}}\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{2^{13} \\times \\binom{52}{26}}{\\binom{104}{26}}\\)", d) "\\(\\frac{2^{26} \\times \\binom{52}{26}}{\\binom{104}{26}}\\)"
R:"Combinatorial selection considering duplicate copies."
}

q {
